query.result:
124 As when, gathering biado or loglio, 125 the doves gathered at the pasture, 126 quiet, without showing the usual pride,
127 if something appears where they have fear, 128 suddenly they leave the bait, 129 because they are assailed by greater care;
130 thus I saw that fresh mob 131 leave the singing, and flee toward the coast, 132 like a man who goes, nor knows where he may escape;
133 nor our party was less tough.
